try =\r\nto address them. *\n&gt; *  *\n&gt; **        *        * *\n&gt; *  *\n&gt; *Maharshi Vasis=\r\nhtha&#39;s teaching to Lord Rama is clear in Yoga Vaasishtham.\n&gt; The goal of ex=\r\nistence and sadhana is self-realization. Siddhis are to be\n&gt; neither specif=\r\nically sought nor specifically avoided, by a seeker of Self.\n&gt; If Nature gi=\r\nves one some siddhi(s), one should accept them with neither\n&gt; excitement no=\r\nr disappointment. But one should NOT run after them, for they\n&gt; are neither=\r\n necessary nor sufficient for self-realization and liberation.\n&gt; *\n&gt; *  *\n&gt;=\r\n *Vivekananda used the same principle when Ramakirishna proposed to give\n&gt; =\r\nhis siddhis to Vivekananda. He asked whether the siddhis will enable him to=\r\n\n&gt; realize god. Ramakrishna said no. Vivekananda firmly declined the offer\n=\r\n&gt; then! Of course, when Ramakrishna gave them anyway later, he accepted the=\r\nm.\n&gt; Vivekananda&#39;s two actions demonstrate Vasishtha&#39;s instructions well. *=\r\n\n&gt; *  *\n&gt; **        *        * *\n&gt; *  *\n&gt; *Let us use the analogy of climbi=\r\nng a hill. Climbing hill is one&#39;s\n&gt; spiritual sadhana. Reaching the top is =\r\nliberation. Different people climb\n&gt; the hill from different sides and usin=\r\ng different paths. There may be trees\n&gt; with nice fruits on the sides of th=\r\ne road. They are siddhis or special\n&gt; abilities. *\n&gt; *  *\n&gt; *If one gets di=\r\nstracted, starts climbing the trees and collecting fruits,\n&gt; one&#39;s journey =\r\ngets delayed and one may not reach the top. That is why\n&gt; Vasishtha says a =\r\nseeker of Self does not pursue any siddhis. *\n&gt; *  *\n&gt; *But if some fruits =\r\nfall in one&#39;s lap by themselves, one can keep them.\n&gt; Similarly, siddhis th=\r\nat come to one by themselves can be accepted by a\n&gt; seeker of Self. *\n&gt; *  =\r\n*\n&gt; *Now an important distinction: *\n&gt; *  *\n&gt; *There are some trees that ar=\r\ne found at lower altitudes also, but some\n&gt; really special trees are found =\r\nat very high altitudes only. If one has such\n&gt; a fruit, it shows that one h=\r\nas climbed great heights. Similarly, some\n&gt; siddhis do not mean much, but s=\r\nome siddhis are very special and only really\n&gt; elevated sadhakas can obtain=\r\n them (whether by trying or without trying). If\n&gt; a sadhakas demonstrates s=\r\nuch a siddhi, you can see that one progressed a\n&gt; lot. However, the key is =\r\nthat one who climbed the same or more distance may\n&gt; not have that or any o=\r\nther fruit. *\n&gt; *  *\n&gt; **        *        * *\n&gt; *  *\n&gt; *Unlike in the examp=\r\nle of climbing hill, which is an external activity,\n&gt; spiritual progress in=\r\n real life is *internal*. There is NO way for anyone to\n&gt; know for sure how=\r\n much progress one has made, how much self-control one has\n&gt; internally and=\r\n what exactly goes on in one&#39;s mind. We may try to judge it\n&gt; from external=\r\n factors such as actions, words etc, but it is not necessarily\n&gt; accurate. =\r\n*\n&gt; *  *\n&gt; *Here, some people swayed by siddhis may be tempted to use one&#39;s=\r\n siddhis\n&gt; to judge how high one climbed. But that is faulty. One person wh=\r\no reached\n&gt; the absolute top may not have any fruits, while one person who =\r\nstill has\n&gt; ways to climb may have gotten some really nice fruit. Using ext=\r\nernaslly\n&gt; demonstrable siddhis that are neither necessary nor sufficient f=\r\nor\n&gt; Self-realization as a measure of one&#39;s progress is unsound. *\n&gt; *  *\n&gt;=\r\n *Given that spiritual progress is internal, how can we judge it and\n&gt; comp=\r\nare people then? Well, we need not and should not. Only a\n&gt; sarvaantaryaami=\r\n - a perfected being who has access to each being&#39;s internal\n&gt; state - can =\r\ndo that. *\n&gt; *  *\n&gt; **        *        * *\n&gt; *  *\n&gt; *Rajarshi, you are assu=\r\nming that Ramakrishna Paramahamsa is a Paramahamsa\n&gt; on Vimalananda&#39;s scale=\r\n. You are concluding that Ramakrishna is a\n&gt; Paramahamsa; Abhedananda, Vive=\r\nkananda etc are lower than that; Vimalananda\n&gt; is a rishi; and hence Vimala=\r\nnanda is superior to Abhedananda and Vivekananda\n&gt; by 2pwr16 to 2. *\n&gt; *  *=\r\n\n&gt; *Is Paramahamsa Nithyananda, who was caught in a sex scandal, also a\n&gt; P=\r\naramahamsa because he is known so? See, how people are famously known may\n&gt;=\r\n or may not reflect their spiritual stature. Real spiritual stature is\n&gt; in=\r\nternal and you cannot see it. *\n&gt; *  *\n&gt; *We do not know who Ramakrishna Pa=\r\nramahamsa really is. He may not be just\n&gt; a paramahamsa on Vimalananda&#39;s sc=\r\nale, but be a siddha or a natha or even a\n&gt; rishi. He may even be Vishnu hi=\r\nmself, as he himself said and some religious\n&gt; experts of that time declare=\r\nd based on various signs. If Ramakrishna\n&gt; Paramahamsa is Vishnu himself, V=\r\nivekananda, Abhedananda etc can definitely\n&gt; be rishis or naths in Vimalana=\r\nnda&#39;s scale. If your argument is that they\n&gt; cannot be because they did not=\r\n demonstrate siddhis compatible with that\n&gt; status, that is a non-point as =\r\nI explained above. The disagreement between\n&gt; then boils down a difference =\r\nin the relevance and importance of externally\n&gt; demonstrated siddhis. *\n&gt; *=\r\n  *\n&gt; **        *        * *\n&gt; *  *\n&gt; *Why this is relevant and I spent som=\r\ne time on this is that some people\n&gt; seem to have misconceptions. The take =\r\nhome for some people from some books\n&gt; describing miracles and siddhis may =\r\nbe that siddhis are important. *\n&gt; *  *\n&gt; *Vasishtha is not only a rishi, b=\r\nut one of saptarshis. Please read what he\n&gt; taught Lord Rama in Yoga Vaasis=\r\nhtham. It is the essence of Veda and\n&gt; Upanishad. It will balance your view=\r\ns and mould your attitude. Read Yoga\n&gt; Vaasishtham. Siddhis are neither nec=\r\nessary nor sufficient for\n&gt; self-realization. Don&#39;t be distracted by them o=\r\nr be infatuated with them.\n&gt; *\n&gt; *  *\n&gt; *The goal of sadhana is that your n=\r\notions of &quot;this is I and these are\n&gt; mine&quot; get subtler and subtler and hold=\r\n of six internal enemies on you\n&gt; becomes weaker and weaker. Others may or =\r\nmay not be able to see and judge\n&gt; your progress, but you know your progres=\r\ns and weaknesses the best. THAT is\n&gt; the crux and siddhis have no relevance=\r\n or meaning. Any fascination for them\n&gt; will set you back in your sadhana. =\r\n*\n&gt; *  *\n&gt; *Best regards, *\n&gt; *Narasimha *\n&gt; *-----------------------------=\r\n-------------------------------------- *\n&gt; *  Free Jyotish Software, Free J=\r\nyotish Lessons, Jyotish Writings, *\n&gt; *&quot;Do It Yourself&quot; ritual manuals for =\r\nshort Homam and Pitri Tarpana: *\n&gt; *                  http://www.VedicAstro=\r\nloger.org&lt;http://www.vedicastrologer.org/&gt;\n&gt; *\n&gt; *     Films that make a di=\r\nfference: http://SaraswatiFilms.org&lt;http://saraswatifilms.org/&gt;\n&gt; *\n&gt; *    =\r\n Spirituality: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/vedic-wisdom *\n&gt; *  Jyotish wr=\r\nitings: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/JyotishWritings *\n&gt; *                =\r\n     Twitter ID: @homam108 *\n&gt; *-------------------------------------------=\r\n------------------------ *\n&gt; *  *\n&gt; *--- In vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com, N=\r\narasimha PVR Rao &lt;pvr@...&gt; wrote: *\n&gt; *&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; Namaste friends, *\n&gt; *&gt; *\n&gt;=\r\n *&gt; There was a long friendly ;-) exchange between Rajarshi and me on\n&gt; Fri=\r\nday *\n&gt; *&gt; (July 29) on twitter on measuring spiritual caliber. This came f=\r\nrom the\n&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; context of Rajarshi&#39;s comments on the &quot;maturity&quot; & &quot;errors=\r\n&quot; of *\n&gt; *&gt; Ramakrishna&#39;s disciples (regarding their attitude towards Tantr=\r\na). He *\n&gt; *&gt; compared them with Vimalananda and said their spiritual calib=\r\ner was of\n&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; the scale of 2, while Vimalananda&#39;s was 2 power 16. He a=\r\nlso talked\n&gt; about *\n&gt; *&gt; the hierarchy of spiritual caliber mentioned by V=\r\n. I want to share 2 *\n&gt; *&gt; cents of musings on that. *\n&gt; *&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; --------=\r\n----------------------- *\n&gt; *&gt; Measuring Spiritual Caliber *\n&gt; *&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; Ra=\r\njarshi, here are a few comments on your statements a couple of days *\n&gt; *&gt; =\r\nback on Twitter comparing spiritual caliber. We can&#39;t even compare *\n&gt; *&gt; f=\r\nlowers like hibiscus, rose, jasmine, mogra, kewda, lotus etc & say *\n&gt; *&gt; w=\r\nhich is a better flower. They have different properties like color, *\n&gt; *&gt; =\r\nsize, shape, number of petals, type/intensity of smell etc. Relative *\n&gt; *&gt;=\r\n values depend on the purpose and they cannot be quantified universally.\n&gt; =\r\n*\n&gt; *&gt; How can any sane person then say that spiritual caliber of different=\r\n *\n&gt; *&gt; people can be compared and quanitified? The field of duality has *\n=\r\n&gt; *&gt; infinite variety and the [self-]control of a yogi has infinite aspects=\r\n\n&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; to it. You cannot quantify the spiritual caliber of a person as o=\r\nne *\n&gt; *&gt; number and compare them. *\n&gt; *&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; Before one even attempts t=\r\no understand Vimalananda&#39;s order (Paramahamsa\n&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; &lt; Siddha &lt; Natha &lt; R=\r\nishi), please note that different hierarchies exist\n&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; in scriptures =\r\nfor deities also. Some consider a hierarchy of deities *\n&gt; *&gt; where Vishnu =\r\nis supreme. Some consider a hierarchy of deities where *\n&gt; *&gt; Shiva is supr=\r\neme. Some consider a hierarchy of deities where Shakti is\n&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; supreme.=\r\n And so on. None of them is absolute. All of them are relative\n&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; and=\r\n for specific purposes, i.e. from a specific perspective. There are\n&gt; *\n&gt; *=\r\n&gt; people who take them as absolute and argue that so and so thing taught\n&gt; =\r\n*\n&gt; *&gt; by Vishnu is superior to so and so thing taught by Shiva, etc. But w=\r\ne *\n&gt; *&gt; know that none of the hierarchies is absolute. *\n&gt; *&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; One w=\r\nho has the nerve to think that one can compare the wisdom of *\n&gt; *&gt; Jnanesh=\r\nwar, dispassion of Ramana Maharshi, mad devotion of Ramakrishna\n&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; Pa=\r\nramahamsa, detached activism of Vivekananda, compassion of Shirdi\n&gt; Sai, *\n=\r\n&gt; *&gt; spiritual ecstasy of Vama Khepa, inner clarity of Lahiri Mahashaya, *\n=\r\n&gt; *&gt; detachment of Trilinga Swami, purity of Tukaram, humility of Eknath *\n=\r\n&gt; *&gt; Maharaj, ecstatic love of Meera Bai, motherly love of Gopaler Ma, etc,=\r\n\n&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; is a fool of the highest order. They can be compared from specifi=\r\nc *\n&gt; *&gt; limited perspectives. In one thing, Tukaram may be superior to all=\r\n, in\n&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; another Jnaneshwar, in another Trilinga, in another Ramakrish=\r\nna, and so\n&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; on. You cannot compare in absolute terms. You should no=\r\nt even try to. *\n&gt; *&gt; You should just appreciate them individually and aspi=\r\nre to be like any\n&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; of them that you like the most. *\n&gt; *&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; Vi=\r\nmalananda&#39;s list may be correct from specific perspective. More *\n&gt; *&gt; impo=\r\nrtantly, his words should make one realize that there is always *\n&gt; *&gt; scop=\r\ne for further self-control (and the resulting mastery over the\n&gt; field *\n&gt; =\r\n*&gt; of duality) while one is still embodied. One should never rest and *\n&gt; *=\r\n&gt; aspire for better self-control. But taking it as gospel and starting to\n&gt;=\r\n *\n&gt; *&gt; judge yogis based on that is unwise. Especially making statements l=\r\nike\n&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; &quot;Vimalananda is heavier than all RK&#39;s discples put togtr&quot; and =\r\nthinking\n&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; that something is absolute truth because Vimalananda is a=\r\nssumed to have\n&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; said that (vs someone &quot;lower than him&quot;) is unwise. =\r\n*\n&gt; *&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; Even if Vimalananda&#39;s hierarchy is absolute and universal, do=\r\nn&#39;t assume\n&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; that you can judge the stature of each yogi accurately.=\r\n Because *\n&gt; *&gt; Ramakrishna was popularly known as a Paramahamsa, is he a P=\r\naramahamsa\n&gt; as *\n&gt; *&gt; per Vimalananda&#39;s classification or a siddha or a na=\r\ntha or even a\n&gt; rishi? *\n&gt; *&gt; Or may be a deity? My friend, don&#39;t assume yo=\r\nu know for sure!!! Based\n&gt; on *\n&gt; *&gt; the details we know, can we be absolut=\r\nely sure of even Vimalananda&#39;s *\n&gt; *&gt; stature based on his own classificati=\r\non? *\n&gt; *&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; You said &quot;Approximating 2 equal to each disciples of rama=\r\nkrishna.\n&gt; 2exp16 *\n&gt; *&gt; =3D say Vimalananda. Basic?&quot; You probably made thi=\r\ns statement based on *\n&gt; *&gt; what you read and heard of Vimalananda. For the=\r\n sake of argument, it is\n&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; not even 100% clear whether he was a real=\r\n person or an imagined *\n&gt; *&gt; character. Svoboda intentionally (and very wi=\r\nsely!) left the latter *\n&gt; *&gt; option open in the preface of his Aghora book=\r\n! *\n&gt; *&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; If we MUST compare spiritual calibers, one possibility is t=\r\no use a *\n&gt; *&gt; simpler definition of how close one is to liberation as a me=\r\nasure of *\n&gt; *&gt; one&#39;s &quot;spiritual caliber&quot;, Ramakrishna&#39;s disciples fare qui=\r\nte well. RK\n&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; told Abhedananda that it was going to be his last birt=\r\nh. Others would\n&gt; be *\n&gt; *&gt; back, but he would be liberated. To Yogananda, =\r\nhe said there would be *\n&gt; *&gt; one more birth and he would be free forever a=\r\nfter that. Vimalananda, on\n&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; the other hand, had atleast one more bi=\r\nrth clearly as he said a body\n&gt; was *\n&gt; *&gt; waiting for him. That way, forge=\r\nt about &quot;RK&#39;s discples put togtr&quot;, just\n&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; Abhedananda alone is super=\r\nior to Vimalananda! *\n&gt; *&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; Again, please note that this is just one =\r\ndefinition. One can have many\n&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; definitions. The key is not to jump =\r\nto unwise conclusions on any *\n&gt; *&gt; hierarchies and say that &quot;X is weightie=\r\nr than Y and so what he said\n&gt; must *\n&gt; *&gt; be more correct&quot;. *\n&gt; *&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; =\r\nPeople with lopsided understanding of scriptures take relative\n&gt; knowledge =\r\n*\n&gt; *&gt; to be absolute and jump to unwise conclusions. I am afraid some peop=\r\nle\n&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; are doing the same now with &quot;modern scriptures&quot; such as the Agh=\r\nora *\n&gt; *&gt; books. Don&#39;t fall into the trap of taking something as gospel or=\r\n as *\n&gt; *&gt; absolute. Written words are always relative and never absolute. =\r\n*\n&gt; *&gt; Discriminate relative knowledge using intellect at first and hopeful=\r\nly\n&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; using experencial realization later on. *\n&gt; *&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; More impo=\r\nrtantly, while we are still searching for &quot;maturity&quot;, we\n&gt; should *\n&gt; *&gt; no=\r\nt commit the &quot;error&quot; of making negative judgmental comments of greats\n&gt; *\n&gt;=\r\n *&gt; who did far more sadhana than us and experienced a lot more than us. *\n=\r\n&gt; *&gt; ------------------------------- *\n&gt; *&gt; *\n&gt; *&gt; Best regards, *\n&gt; *&gt; Nar=\r\nasimha *\n&gt;\n&gt; \n&gt;\n\r\n--0015174c395ee6a77404a99f2773\r\nContent-Type: text/html; charset=windows-1252\r\nContent-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable\r\n\r\n&lt;div&gt;Namaste Narasimhaji,&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;=A0&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;Thank you so much for y=\r\nour lucid explanations of these key points, which are important though subt=\r\nle. This is in perfect consonance with what I have learned from my guru and=\r\n various acharyas from whom I have been privileged to learn. For moksha, ev=\r\nen samadhi is not required, let alone any siddhis.&lt;/div&gt;\n\n\n&lt;div&gt;=A0&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;=\r\ndiv&gt;Warm regards,&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;Aditi&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div class=3D&quot;gmail_quote&quot;=\r\n&gt;On Wed, Aug 3, 2011 at 3:43 PM, Narasimha PVR Rao &lt;span dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;&lt;a=\r\n href=3D&quot;mailto:pvr@...&quot;&gt;pvr@...&lt;/a&gt;&gt;&lt;/span&gt; wrote:&lt;br&gt;\n=\r\n&lt;blockquote style=3D&quot;BORDER-LEFT: #ccc 1px solid; MARGIN: 0px 0px 0px 0.8ex=\r\n; PADDING-LEFT: 1ex&quot; class=3D&quot;gmail_quote&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;/u&gt;\n&lt;div style=3D&quot;BACKGROUND=\r\n-COLOR: #fff&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;=A0&lt;/span&gt; \n&lt;div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;=\r\nfont color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;Namaste,&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;d=\r\niv align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;=A0&lt;/=\r\nfont&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;=\r\nVerdana&quot;&gt;An interesting point came up in a private exchange with a couple o=\r\nf folks and I will write it down for the benefit of others.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;d=\r\niv align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;=A0&lt;/=\r\nfont&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;=\r\nVerdana&quot;&gt;*=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0=A0 *&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/