y consistent with Upanishadic learni=\r\nng. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; =\r\nface=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;=A0 &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#0000=\r\n00&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;You talk about taking the words of a great =\r\ninstead of speculating. In fact, did Vimalananda *explicitly* write that Ra=\r\nmakrishna is only a &quot;Paramahamsa&quot; and not a siddha or a natha or =\r\na rishi, that Vivekananda is not a rishi or natha or siddha or paramahamsa,=\r\n and so on? In my case, my statement above is explicitly and unambiguously =\r\nstated by Vasishtha. By answering Vivekananda&#39;s question &quot;will sid=\r\ndhis help me in god realization&quot; in the negative, Ramakrishna also aff=\r\nirmed this teaching of Vasishtha. Krishna also essentially refers to the sa=\r\nme thing in Bhagavad Gita when he talks about seeking small things from dem=\r\nigods vs seeking &quot;me&quot; (Self). Vaishtha&#39;s words, however, are =\r\nthe clearest and most unambiguous. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;fon=\r\nt color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;=A0 &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div alig=\r\nn=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;Yoga Vaasish=\r\ntham was taught by Vasishtha to Lord Rama in the presence of Vishwamitra an=\r\nd other great sages and recorded by Valmiki. It is the highest watermark of=\r\n spiritual knowledge. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#0=\r\n00000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;=A0 &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;f=\r\nont color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;Aghora series is nice, bu=\r\nt can give wrong notions to some who may tend to be fascinated by external =\r\nmiracles. I have no doubt that Vimalananda had no confusions himself, but s=\r\nome people reading those books can form misconceptions (though it is still =\r\nok if that makes them do sadhana. The only problem is if they start doing t=\r\nhe bad karma of making negative judgments on greats thinking they are blind=\r\nly following Vimalananda). It is a good idea to balance the perspective wit=\r\nh some Vedantic understanding such as Yoga Vasishtham or Bhagavad Gita. &lt;/f=\r\nont&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D=\r\n&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;=A0 &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; siz=\r\ne=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&gt; Infact it also violates a point which you you=\r\nrself made in an earlier mail. The &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font =\r\ncolor=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&gt; external is connected to=\r\n the internal. Some siddhis are not possible unless one &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div =\r\nalign=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&gt; att=\r\nains a very rarified level of realization. And they manifest externally. &lt;/=\r\nfont&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;=\r\nVerdana&quot;&gt;=A0 &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=\r\n=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;Yes, some external siddhis are possible only at a v=\r\nery rarefied level of realization. But some with the same or higher level o=\r\nf realization may not possess the same external siddhi. Thus external mirac=\r\nles cannot be used as measures of one&#39;s level. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n\n&lt;div ali=\r\ngn=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;=A0 &lt;/font&gt;=\r\n&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verda=\r\nna&quot;&gt;This is like the analogy I gave of collecting fruits from the trees on =\r\nthe side of the road to the hilltop. Some keep tavelling on the road and ac=\r\ncept only those fruits that land in their lap by themselves. Some get distr=\r\nacted from the journey and pursue the fruits actively. Collecting fruits is=\r\n neither necessary nor sufficient for reaching the top. Though having a fru=\r\nit that is available only at a very high altitude shows that one has reache=\r\nd great altitude, it cannot be used as a measure of one&#39;s progress, for=\r\n someone may have climbed greater heights without collecting that (or any) =\r\nfruit. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;=\r\n2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;=A0 &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#0=\r\n00000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;External and internal do NOT have a one-=\r\nto-one correspondence. Just as you cannot tell what is inside a house by lo=\r\noking at it from outside, so cannot you tell one&#39;s state of mind from l=\r\nooking at one. One&#39;s spiritual maturity and attainment is in one&#39;s =\r\nstate of mind. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; =\r\nsize=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;=A0 &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div align=3D&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;font col=\r\nor=3D&quot;#000000&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;*=A0=A0=A0=A